1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:02:02,140 --> 00:02:05,520
So, take me with you
when you set sail, Shanks!

3
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:07,570
I wanna be a pirate, too!

4
00:02:09,190 --> 00:02:11,400
Like you'd ever make it as a pirate!

5
00:02:11,820 --> 00:02:13,200
Why not?!

6
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:15,570
Luffy.

7
00:02:15,570 --> 00:02:19,620
Just bein' a good swimmer doesn't
mean you're pirate material.

8
00:02:19,620 --> 00:02:23,160
I'm good at fighting too!
My punches are like pistols!

9
00:02:23,160 --> 00:02:24,670
Oh, really?

10
00:02:24,670 --> 00:02:26,130
What's that supposed to mean?!

11
00:02:26,460 --> 00:02:29,130
He means you're just
too young, Luffy!

12
00:02:29,130 --> 00:02:31,590
Seriously, you're the same
age as my own kid!

13
00:02:31,590 --> 00:02:33,970
I'm not a little kid! I'm a grownup!

14
00:02:33,970 --> 00:02:35,680
Hey, now. Simmer down.

15
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:37,390
Here, have some juice.

16
00:02:37,390 --> 00:02:39,350
Oh! Thanks!

17
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:42,810
See?! You are just a kid! Hilarious!

18
00:02:42,810 --> 00:02:44,480
No fair, Shanks!

19
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:47,770
Don't laugh!

20
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,440
Shanks, you suck!

21
00:02:55,610 --> 00:02:57,160
Excuse us.

22
00:03:00,620 --> 00:03:03,370
Oh... So, these are "pirates."

23
00:03:03,370 --> 00:03:05,460
Looks like a sorry bunch to me.

24
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:09,250
Welcome.

25
00:03:09,630 --> 00:03:11,550
We're mountain bandits,

26
00:03:11,550 --> 00:03:14,260
but we ain't here to bust up the place.

27
00:03:14,630 --> 00:03:17,470
Sell us some booze.
Ten barrels oughta do.

28
00:03:18,550 --> 00:03:22,390
My apologies.
I just ran out of alcohol.

29
00:03:22,390 --> 00:03:24,020
That's odd.

30
00:03:24,020 --> 00:03:27,600
Then what are these
pirates drinking? Water?

31
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:31,070
I'm afraid I served
the last of it to them.

32
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:35,610
I feel bad. Looks like we drank
the whole place dry.

33
00:03:35,950 --> 00:03:36,610
Sorry!

34
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:40,870
You can have this.
It hasn't been opened yet.

35
00:03:46,710 --> 00:03:50,380
My head's worth
eight million berries, you know.

36
00:03:50,380 --> 00:03:54,340
One bottle ain't even enough for
a nightcap! Don't insult me!

37
00:03:58,090 --> 00:03:59,590
The floor's all wet!

38
00:04:00,850 --> 00:04:04,020
Sorry about the mess, Makino.
Do you have a rag?

39
00:04:04,020 --> 00:04:06,520
Oh, Leave that to me!

40
00:04:12,570 --> 00:04:14,690
Seems you like to clean.

41
00:04:14,690 --> 00:04:17,320
Maybe you'll find this more fulfilling.

42
00:04:18,740 --> 00:04:22,240
Not worth our time if they're
out of booze. Let's go!

43
00:04:24,660 --> 00:04:26,750
Later, cowards!

44
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:36,630
Are you all right?
Did they hurt you, Captain?

45
00:04:36,630 --> 00:04:38,840
Yeah, I'm fine. No worries.

46
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,760
He got you good, Chief!

47
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:46,310
Talk about lame!

48
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:50,900
Why are you laughing?!

49
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:53,310
That was so uncool!

50
00:04:53,310 --> 00:04:55,230
Why didn't you fight back?!

51
00:04:55,610 --> 00:04:57,990
No matter how many there are
or how strong they seem,

52
00:04:57,990 --> 00:05:01,820
you can't call yourself a man or a pirate
if you laugh after something like that!

53
00:05:03,570 --> 00:05:05,700
I get where you're coming from...

54
00:05:06,330 --> 00:05:08,450
but he only got some booze on me.

55
00:05:08,450 --> 00:05:10,410
It's nothing worth getting mad over.

56
00:05:10,410 --> 00:05:11,540
Whatever!

57
00:05:19,880 --> 00:05:21,880
Eating your feelings, Luffy?

58
00:05:21,260 --> 00:05:21,880
Shut up!

59
00:05:24,390 --> 00:05:25,850
Wait, what're you eating?!

60
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:31,390
That box! Did you eat
what was in that box?!

61
00:05:31,390 --> 00:05:32,400
I-I did...

62
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:36,070
Spit it out! Right now! Every last bite!

63
00:05:36,070 --> 00:05:38,530
Wh-What're you doing, Shanks?!

64
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:46,080
What... just happened?

65
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:48,950
You just ate the Gum-Gum Fruit!

66
00:05:48,950 --> 00:05:50,750
It's known as a devil fruit!

67
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:52,750
You gain a rubber body after eating it,

68
00:05:52,750 --> 00:05:56,670
but you lose the ability
to swim for life!

69
00:05:56,670 --> 00:05:59,130
What?! No way!

70
00:05:59,130 --> 00:06:01,050
You dumbass!

71
00:06:10,770 --> 00:06:14,020
People were drinkin'
and havin' a nice time.

72
00:06:14,020 --> 00:06:16,360
What's the big idea, boy?

73
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:18,070
Dammit! Apologize!

74
00:06:18,070 --> 00:06:19,860
Don't make fun of
Shanks and his crew!

75
00:06:22,030 --> 00:06:25,360
Did I say something to offend you?

76
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:27,160
You did! Now apologize!

77
00:06:27,660 --> 00:06:28,620
Mayor!

78
00:06:33,620 --> 00:06:36,420
You see the looks on
those pirates' faces?!

79
00:06:36,420 --> 00:06:39,380
All drenched in booze
with nothin' to say!

80
00:06:39,380 --> 00:06:41,050
Talk about pathetic!

81
00:06:41,260 --> 00:06:43,970
Pirates ain't nothin' but cowards.

82
00:06:43,970 --> 00:06:45,550
All bark and no bite.

83
00:06:45,550 --> 00:06:46,800
Cut it out!

84
00:06:48,510 --> 00:06:51,930
Stop making fun of Shanks
and his crew! They're not cowards!

85
00:06:51,930 --> 00:06:53,480
Calm down, Luffy!

86
00:06:55,650 --> 00:06:58,270
Stop making fun of Shanks
and his crew, stupid bandits!

87
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:06,030
You oughta watch your mouth, boy.

88
00:07:06,030 --> 00:07:10,410
No one's ever made me mad
and lived to tell the tale.

89
00:07:10,410 --> 00:07:12,500
Wait!

90
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:15,000
Let the boy go! I beg you!

91
00:07:17,170 --> 00:07:21,420
I don't know what Luffy has done,
but I have no intention of fighting you.

92
00:07:21,420 --> 00:07:23,300
If you allow it, I'll even pay you!

93
00:07:23,300 --> 00:07:26,680
Just, please! Spare the boy's life!

94
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,090
The mayor!

95
00:07:28,590 --> 00:07:32,310
Leave it to a senior citizen
to know the ways of the world.

96
00:07:32,310 --> 00:07:34,980
But no, it's too late for that now,

97
00:07:34,980 --> 00:07:37,980
not after he's pissed me off.

98
00:07:38,810 --> 00:07:41,320
You're the bad guys here,
you mountain apes!

99
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:47,240
You're a lost cause, kid. You can
regret all this in the next life!

100
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,070
Luffy!

101
00:07:48,070 --> 00:07:50,870
Please! Let him go!

102
00:07:50,870 --> 00:07:53,950
I was wondering why
the bar was empty...

103
00:07:54,910 --> 00:07:56,790
If it isn't those mountain bandits.

104
00:07:57,250 --> 00:07:59,000
Captain!

105
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:04,880
Shanks!

106
00:08:05,420 --> 00:08:08,930
So you pirates are still here, huh?

107
00:08:08,930 --> 00:08:11,390
Been busy scrubbing
down the village?

108
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:12,390
Luffy...

109
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:15,600
I thought your punches
were as strong as pistols.

110
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,730
Shut up!

111
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:21,480
I dunno why you're here, but you'd
best leave before you get hurt.

112
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:25,360
Any closer and you're dead meat, coward!

113
00:08:26,530 --> 00:08:29,160
What are you, deaf?

114
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:30,490
I'll blow your head off!

115
00:08:32,780 --> 00:08:34,620
Put your life on the line.

116
00:08:34,990 --> 00:08:35,660
Huh?!

117
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:38,960
You've drawn your pistol,
so put your life on the line.

118
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:41,210
Huh? The hell do you mean?

119
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:44,710
I'm saying those are for more
than just threatening someone.

120
00:08:54,890 --> 00:08:56,520
N-Now you've done it!

121
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:58,060
These bastards fight dirty!

122
00:08:58,060 --> 00:08:59,190
"Dirty"?

123
00:08:59,190 --> 00:09:01,060
Cut the crap.

124
00:09:01,060 --> 00:09:03,770
You think you're dealing with saints?

125
00:09:03,770 --> 00:09:06,480
You're looking at pirates!

126
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:09,650
Shut up! This is none of your
damn business anyway!

127
00:09:09,650 --> 00:09:11,490
Listen, bandits.

128
00:09:11,490 --> 00:09:16,040
Whether I'm doused in alcohol,
covered in food, or even spit on,

129
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:18,580
most of the time, I'll just laugh it off.

130
00:09:18,580 --> 00:09:19,620
But know this!

131
00:09:19,620 --> 00:09:21,620
No matter the reason...

132
00:09:21,620 --> 00:09:24,000
if you hurt my friends,
you'll pay dearly!

133
00:09:25,130 --> 00:09:26,210
Shanks...

134
00:09:28,460 --> 00:09:30,050
Pay dearly, huh?!

135
00:09:30,050 --> 00:09:33,220
Lousy pirates! Kill 'em, men!

136
00:09:35,470 --> 00:09:37,680
I'll handle this. Piece of cake.

137
00:09:47,940 --> 00:09:50,150
Don't get cocky, bandit.

138
00:09:50,150 --> 00:09:54,740
If you wanna fight us,
at least bring a battleship.

139
00:09:55,620 --> 00:09:57,200
So strong!

140
00:09:57,200 --> 00:10:01,620
H-Hold on! The kid attacked us!

141
00:10:01,620 --> 00:10:03,210
You're a wanted man, aren't you?

142
00:10:04,380 --> 00:10:05,250
Dammit!

143
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:07,840
A smokescreen?!

144
00:10:11,340 --> 00:10:12,300
Luffy!

145
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:16,050
Crap! I let my guard down!
He got Luffy!

146
00:10:16,050 --> 00:10:17,810
What do we do, guys?!

147
00:10:17,810 --> 00:10:19,930
Quit freakin' the hell out, Chief!

148
00:10:19,930 --> 00:10:22,940
If we all look,
we'll find him in no time!

149
00:10:22,940 --> 00:10:26,400
I can't believe this guy...

150
00:10:28,150 --> 00:10:30,030
I made a clean getaway!

151
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:33,030
They'd never expect a mountain
bandit to escape by sea!

152
00:10:33,030 --> 00:10:35,700
Dammit! Let me go, you stupid ape!

153
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:37,370
I hope you die!

154
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:40,580
You dumbass! You're the one
who's about to die!

155
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:43,540
After all, you pissed me off!

156
00:10:43,870 --> 00:10:45,000
So long!

157
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,340
Dammit! Dammit!

158
00:10:48,340 --> 00:10:52,130
I couldn't land a single hit on those scumbags! Dammit!

159
00:10:57,510 --> 00:11:01,390
Sorry! I got no use for you anymore!

160
00:11:09,860 --> 00:11:12,440
Wh-What the hell?!

161
00:11:19,330 --> 00:11:21,450
Help!

162
00:11:37,970 --> 00:11:39,300
Shanks...

163
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:48,770
Get lost!

164
00:12:02,740 --> 00:12:04,250
I'm in your debt, Luffy...

165
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,830
Makino told me everything.

166
00:12:07,370 --> 00:12:09,580
You stood up for us.

167
00:12:13,210 --> 00:12:16,590
C'mon, don't cry! You're a man, right?

168
00:12:16,590 --> 00:12:18,720
But... Shanks...

169
00:12:19,470 --> 00:12:22,430
Your arm!

170
00:12:22,810 --> 00:12:25,640
It's only an arm. No big deal.

171
00:12:26,430 --> 00:12:27,810
I'm just glad you're not hurt.

172
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:50,370
You're leaving, then?

173
00:12:50,370 --> 00:12:51,790
Yeah.

174
00:12:51,790 --> 00:12:54,710
We were able to stay awhile,
but it's time to part ways.

175
00:12:54,710 --> 00:12:55,880
Bet you'll miss me, huh?

176
00:12:55,880 --> 00:13:00,930
Well, yeah, but I'm not gonna
ask you to take me this time.

177
00:13:00,930 --> 00:13:04,050
I've decided to become
a pirate on my own!

178
00:13:05,810 --> 00:13:07,890
I wasn't gonna take you anyway!

179
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:10,810
You'll never make it as a pirate!

180
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:12,350
Will too!

181
00:13:13,110 --> 00:13:16,360
Someday, I'm gonna gather a crew
every bit as good as yours.

182
00:13:16,730 --> 00:13:18,820
We'll find the world's greatest treasure...

183
00:13:19,570 --> 00:13:22,530
and then, I'll show you!
I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!

184
00:13:23,490 --> 00:13:24,370
Oh?

185
00:13:24,370 --> 00:13:26,200
You're gonna surpass us, huh?

186
00:13:29,330 --> 00:13:30,080
In that case...

187
00:13:32,920 --> 00:13:34,790
I'll leave this hat with you.

188
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:37,630
It means a lot to me.

189
00:13:38,260 --> 00:13:39,550
Take good care of it!

190
00:13:59,610 --> 00:14:02,650
Come bring it back to me someday...

191
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:06,280
once you've become a great pirate!

192
00:14:07,410 --> 00:14:09,950
That's our promise, Luffy!
